   "source": [
    "# 22. How do you measure the accuracy of a recommendation engine?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ef2a6878",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Measuring a recommendation engine isn’t just about “accuracy”—it depends on what you care about: predicting ratings correctly or recommending the right items.\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 1. Rating Prediction Metrics (When predicting ratings)\n",
    "\n",
    "If your system predicts ratings (like 1–5 stars):\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error)\n",
    "Penalizes large errors more\n",
    "Lower = better\n",
    "🔹 MAE (Mean Absolute Error)\n",
    "Average absolute difference\n",
    "Less sensitive to outliers\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Used when exact rating prediction matters\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 2. Ranking Metrics (Most Important in real-world)\n",
    "\n",
    "In practice, recommendations are about top-N items, not exact ratings.\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Precision@K\n",
    "Out of top K recommendations, how many are relevant?\n",
    "🔥 Recall@K\n",
    "Out of all relevant items, how many were recommended?\n",
    "🔥 F1-score@K\n",
    "Balance of precision and recall\n",
    "🔹 MAP (Mean Average Precision)\n",
    "Evaluates ranking quality across users\n",
    "🔹 NDCG (Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain)\n",
    "Gives higher weight to items ranked at the top\n",
    "\n",
    "✔️ Very important in companies like Netflix and Amazon\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ 3. Business / Online Metrics (Real-world impact)\n",
    "\n",
    "These matter the most in production:\n",
    "\n",
    "CTR (Click Through Rate)\n",
    "Conversion Rate\n",
    "Revenue / Sales uplift\n",
    "User engagement / watch time\n",
    "✅ 4. Diversity & Novelty Metrics\n",
    "Diversity → Are recommendations varied?\n",
    "Novelty → Are you showing new/unseen items?\n",
    "🎯 Interview-Ready Answer (Short)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Recommendation systems are evaluated using rating prediction metrics like RMSE and MAE, ranking metrics like Precision@K, Recall@K, and NDCG, and business metrics such as CTR and conversion rate. In practice, ranking and business metrics are more important than pure accuracy.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip\n",
    "\n",
    "Say this line in interview 👇\n",
    "👉 “A model with low RMSE is not always a good recommender—ranking quality matters more.”"
   ]
  },
